The article discusses the White House Conference on Bullying Prevention and the efforts being made to address bullying. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama emphasize the importance of taking steps to prevent bullying and create a safe environment for all students. The article highlights various private, non-profit, and federal commitments to bullying prevention, including initiatives by Formspring and MIT to detect online bullying, MTV's anti-digital discrimination coalition, Facebook's new safety features, SurveyMonkey's survey tool for collecting information about bullying, and campaigns by the National Education Association, American Federation of Teachers, National PTA, National Association of Student Councils, and National School Boards Association. The article also mentions the Federal Partners in Bullying Prevention Steering Committee and their activities, including the launch of the StopBullying.gov website and the issuance of guidance on enforcing civil rights laws and shaping state laws and policies.